<br>
After fighting for weeks in KC, I had a nearly complete set of flayed skin armour for a ShadowKnight so I paid for a port to Toxxulia Forest, ran to Erudin, and took the boat to Qeynos to make a human Shadowknight and transfer equipment to him.<br>
<br>
I entered a house with both chars and put them in a room upstairs, nice and quiet, practically no risk of being surprising by someone while swapping chars (it wasn't a busy period and I knew no one there to give the stuff to).<br>
<br>
There was just a sewer rat nearby, but it didn't try to attack my level 51 enchantress. Anyway I started putting down the equipment one piece at a time and each time I saw a message saying that the sewer rat went &quot;squeek squeek&quot;. That started to get me worried, it dawned on me that each squeek came after I dropped something on the ground, so I looked to see if anything was missing. EVERYTHING was missing, not one object on the ground.<br>
<br>
So either I was too near the wall and the objects were inside the wall or had fallen downstairs, or the rat had stolen the stuff. I had heard of NPCs stealing stuff, but I'd never considered a rat as being a NPC, I mean it's just an animal like all animals we fight, not a named one even.<br>
<br>
Anyway I ran downstairs to see if items had fallen down, nothing, looked outside the building, nothing. So, thought I, it must be the sewer rat. I rushed back up, found the rat and killed it to loot back my stuff. Arrgh, just whiskers on it. Not my equipment. So the rat had just eaten the armour pieces and the weapon ??? Now how the heck could a rat eat up a metallic 2h axe ??? I could imagine with a big effort that it could eat flayed skin armor, but a metal axe ? No way, my imagination just can't go that far, lol.<br>
<br>
So I petitioned and a guy answered after a while. He explained that indeed the rat must have eaten everything and there was of course nothing he could do about it. All creatures are NPCs, just like the merchants and guards, and NPCs love stealing any loot dropped on the ground. And rats eat every known substance in Norrath.<br>
<br>
They are probably more formidable than dragons <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway I scrapped my SHD.<br>
<br>
Jaelle, enchantress on Zeb<br>
